    "John T. Carroll": "), that is, as a brief\nnarrative set alongside a reality that it illuminates (here, compact story-like\nimages that function as metaphors). Each miniparable imagines a hypothetical\nsituation that common sense recognizes as unthinkable. Nobody would be fool-\nish enough to tear a patch from a new garment so as to mend an old one, for\nthat would result in the ruin of a new garment and a poor fit between patch and\nold garment (",
